      "created_at": "2021-12-01T12:10:17.649Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Cool, yes we are planning on changing that meaning either you are only in auto-pause mode or only in manual start mode.   So in your cause it sounds like you would just leave the setting to always be in auto-pause /auto-start.  Most people would stay this way.  It causes some people problems because we allow both right now and you are not sure if you are in auto pause mode or in manual pause/start mode\u2026  And if it is in the background it can be a real problem if you accidentally pressed start instead of auto-start.</p>",
